        "paragraph_index": 0,
        "text": "SRD-46 shows a **clear increase** in the reported **cumulative log β** values for the Ni²⁺–ethylenediamine system as ionic strength rises, at roughly room temperature.\n\n| Ionic strength range, I (M) | log β₁ for ML | log β₂ for ML₂ | log β₃ for ML₃ |\n|---|---:|---:|---:|\n| ~0 (`-0.15` to `0.15`) | 7.32 | 13.50 | 17.61 |\n| ~0–0.25 | 7.30 | 13.40 | 17.51 |\n| 0.35–0.65 | 7.45 | 13.77 | 18.05 |\n| 0.85–1.15 | 7.56 | 14.05 | 18.29 |\n| 1.85–2.15 | 7.90 | 14.53 | 19.18* |\n| 2.85–3.15 | 7.87 | 14.53 | 19.18 |\n\n\\*The network summary reports upper values consistent with the high-I trend; the stability search summary gives overall room-temperature ranges of **7.3–7.9**, **13.4–14.53**, and **17.51–19.18** for ML, ML₂, and ML₃ respectively.",
